Architecture from the period of Great Migrations to classicist architecture (Roman, Gothic, Renaissance, Mannerism, Baroque, Rococo, Classicism). Historicism (neostyles). The early period of development of modern architecture. Urbanization, utilitarian architecture. Stylistics issues at the end of the 19th /at the beginning of the 20th century (Jugendstil, Arts and Crafts Movement). Modernism of the beginning of the 20th century (Expressionism, Functionalism, de Stijl, Bauhaus, Le Corbusier, Russian Constructivism, Traditionalism, Classicism of the Nordic countries). Post-war rebuilding (International style). Wooden architecture. Estonian architecture from Middle Age to 21. century.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Students get an overview of the history of architecture since the medieval period until today, both in Estonia and around the world.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course students: -	differentiate between historical styles of architecture; -	know and distinguish between different styles in architecture according to regions; -	can name the types of buildings; -	know the influences of industry, urbanization and globalization to the architecture in the 20th century; -	can search for and use relevant reference materials. -       understands the links between socioeconomic changes and changes in the architectural environment
